10 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION - LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL - ADVANCED NUCLEAR
11 ENERGY STUDY - MATCHING FUNDS - ONE-TIME FUNDING. There is appropriated out of
12 any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of
13 $300,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, and from special funds derived from
14 grants or donations from nonstate sources, the sum of $300,000, or so much of the sum as may
15 be necessary, to the legislative council for the purpose of contracting for consulting services for
16 the study provided for in section 1 of this Act, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and
17 ending June 30, 2027. The legislative council shall seek matching funds from the private sector
18 to the extent available to assist with the cost of the project. The funding provided in this section
19 is considered a one-time funding item.
